(C) Under the contract or certification, the private 203
cybersecurity firm shall do all of the following: 204
(1) Register in Ohio and be in good standing with the 205
secretary of state; 206
(2) Provide proof of insurance coverage including 207
cybersecurity liability coverage; 208
(3) Employ staff with relevant certifications. At least 209
one staff member of the private cybersecurity firm shall possess 210
certification from at least one of the following: the certified 211
information systems security professional (CISSP), certified 212
information security manager (CISM), certified information 213
systems auditor (CISA), global information assurance 214
certification (GIAC), offensive security certified professional 215
(OSCP), service organization control (SOC) 2, or an equivalent. 216
(4) Demonstrate proficiency in cybersecurity frameworks 217
such as any of the following: the national institute of 218
standards and technology cybersecurity framework (NIST CSF), 219
national institute of standards and technology (NIST) 800-53, 220
center for internet security (CIS) controls, or international 221
organization for standardization (ISO) 27001; 222
